<br>
That is my responsibility as a parent. It is also my job to always know where they are, who they are with and what they are doing. Granted this is easier for me because I also homeschool. Until my child is 18 and not living in my house, thier buisness is my buisness. They have to earn respect by showing respect, they earn privledges by showing responsibility. All these things must remain consistant too.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is, I have to do my job 24/7. If someones kid is not doing well in school, is getting into trouble with the law, is doing drugs, then the parent is not doing something right. I don't care if that means you have to follow your kid around at school, search thier room or any other &quot;extreme&quot; measure, when you have kids, they are your first priority.<br>
<br>
So in answer to your question. Yes, it is the parents fault. Because they did not fulfill thier responsibility. <p>Crackanna Breeze<BR>
